text: Comforting bowl of mee pok. Always add extra bean sprouts. Love that they have a separate bigger bowl of all the ingredients. For $4 i think it's value for money

Good ole heartland neighbourhood coffeeshop. The malay food is reliable, available and decent value.

Drink counter is efficient and friendly.
Has a smoking area which is great for the uncles and workers. Hope the local MP does not mess with this. leave well enough alone.

Good vibe where many people know each other and look forward to catch up regularly.
Tried the laksa and it's good. Portion is great for the price.
Went there for the kway chap & braised duck, braised pork plus others u will order to accompany the kway chap. Have been a regular customer for a long time since I lived nearby.

This coffee shop has the A&C Kway Chap, a minced pork noodle store, economic beeHoon, Muslim food and Indian food.

Seat places are very cramped here but the food choices and quality makes up for it.

Had the minced pork noodles today at the Yong Soon Noodle store. Theirs is a chilli base version instead of the usual vinegar type.

Yums
